      "actor": "user",
      "content": "You are a subagent. I am the orchestrator.\n\nYou are the subagent named: Wave 3 — Narrow Import Migration\nYou MUST fulfill this task within the boundaries set below. Do not deviate.\n\n## Context\nPhase 24.3.2 is fixing 6 critical flaws in execute-slash-command tool. Wave 1 (Zod schema, typed errors) and Wave 2 (session tools move) are COMPLETE.\n\nWave 3 is the FINAL wave: **Narrow Import Migration** — migrate 24 tool files to use narrow/precise imports instead of wildcard/broad imports.\n\n## Task\nRead `24.3.2-PLAN.md` and `24.3.2-SPEC.md` to understand the narrow import migration requirements. Then:\n\n### Step 1: Identify 24 tool files requiring migration\n- Look for imports like: `import * as X from \"...\"` or `import { a, b, c } from \"...\"` (broad imports)\n- Replace with: `import { X } from \"...\"` or `import X from \"...\"` (narrow imports)\n- Files are in `src/tools/hivemind/` and `src/tools/session/` (excluding the 4 already moved session tools)\n\n### Step 2: For each file requiring migration:\n1. Read the file\n2. Identify broad imports\n3. Replace with narrow imports\n4. Verify typecheck passes\n5. Verify tests pass\n\n### Step 3: Test\n- Run `npm run typecheck` — must pass\n- Run `npm test` — must pass (2559 tests)\n\n### Step 4: Commit\n- Commit message: `phase: 24.3.2 W3 — narrow import migration for 24 tools`\n\n## Constraints:\n- Only migrate imports — do NOT change file logic\n- Keep the same functionality — only change import style\n- Each narrow import should be a single named import or default import\n- Do NOT introduce new dependencies or change export paths\n\n## Done Criteria:\n- All 24 tool files have narrow imports\n- `npm run typecheck` passes\n- `npm test` passes (2559 tests)\n- Commit created with correct message\n\n## IMPORTANT:\n- This is the FINAL wave — after this, Phase 24.3.2 is COMPLETE\n- Do NOT start any new features or changes\n- Only import migration\n- Read the spec and plan files first\n\nExecute this task now. Return your result when done.",
